pgbackup is a simple backup manager for postgresql

-

how to use ?

1 - clone this git repo:
$ cd ~
$ git clone git@github.com:lucasdavila/pgbackup.git
$ cd pgbackup

2 - create your schedules in schedules folder:
$ echo 'put your backup command here' >> schedules/my_schedule_name

ex:

echo '/usr/bin/pg_dump --host localhost --port 5432 --username "postgres" --format custom --blobs --verbose --file "/home/lucasdavila/backups/my_file_backup_name-%(now)s.backup" my_db_name' >> schedules/my_super_schedule

